I expected Hillary Clinton to win, and I had resigned myself to the fact that she would be this nation’s first female President.
The 2016 election was a wild ride dominated at times by discussion of America electing a female President.
We’re in the midst of a global pandemic, but not even this can stop some American politicians from indulging in identity politics.
Given that Biden is seventy-seven years old, his selection of a Vice President is crucial.
Surely America will see a female serve as Vice President and President in the coming years.